@startuml
title Viaverse Payment / Wallet — Use Case Diagram
left to right direction

actor Requester
actor "Worker / Business" as Worker
actor "Payment Provider\niyzico / Stripe" as Provider
actor "Masterpass / Wallet" as Masterpass
actor "Payment Admin" as Admin

rectangle "Payment / Wallet Boundary" {
  usecase "Accept quote" as Accept
  usecase "Create payment session" as Session
  usecase "Choose payment method" as Method
  usecase "Open provider checkout" as Checkout
  usecase "Pay with saved card\ntokenized" as Saved
  usecase "Add card token\nwithout PAN/CVV storage" as AddCard
  usecase "Verify provider callback" as Callback
  usecase "Authorize / capture payment" as Capture
  usecase "Handle payment failure" as Failure
  usecase "Calculate commission\n5% initial" as Commission
  usecase "Hold payout until completion" as Hold
  usecase "Show payment status" as Status
  usecase "Refund / partial refund" as Refund
  usecase "Release payout" as Payout
  usecase "Audit payment admin action" as Audit
}

Requester --> Accept
Accept --> Session
Session --> Method
Method --> Checkout : new payment
Method ..> Saved : saved method
Method ..> AddCard : add card
Checkout --> Callback
Callback --> Capture
Saved --> Capture
Capture --> Commission : success
Capture ..> Failure : failure
Commission --> Hold
Hold --> Status
Worker --> Status
Admin --> Refund
Admin --> Payout
Refund --> Audit
Payout --> Audit
Provider --> Checkout
Provider --> Callback
Masterpass --> AddCard

note bottom
Viaverse never stores PAN/CVV.
Stored cards are provider tokens only.
Callback verification + idempotency are mandatory.
end note
@enduml
